A man from Christiana in the Northern Cape who was kidnapped on Thursday has been&nbsp;rescued by police.Four suspects forced the man to withdraw money from his accounts.Northern Cape police spokesperson Philani Nkwalase says more withdrawal's were made from his investment account.The man was then forced to request "huge withdrawals" at a Nedbank in Kimberley but the bank denied these.Nkwalase said once police became aware of the matter, action was taken and the man's bank card was blocked to prevent further withdrawals from ATMs.A task team, including the Hawks and provincial detectives, was set up.They managed to rescue the man at a Nedbank in New Park at 11.30.The suspects ran away and officers are trying to locate them.The Hawks are investigating charges of extortion, kidnapping and robbery.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/police-task-team-rescues-kidnapped-man-20170528